Heidi backend default: http://127.0.0.1:7777


Heidi UI default: http://127.0.0.1:3002 (strictPort)


UI must not hardcode ports; backend base comes from env: VITE_HEIDI_SERVER_BASE (primary), HEIDI_SERVER_BASE (fallback), default http://127.0.0.1:7777


UI calls backend via /api/* only (/api/health, /api/run, /api/loop, /api/runs, /api/runs/:id, /api/runs/:id/stream)


CLI paths: global config (HEIDI_HOME override; Linux ~/.config/heidi, macOS ~/Library/Application Support/Heidi, Windows %APPDATA%\Heidi), tasks stay in project ./tasks


Add CLI lifecycle commands: heidi update, heidi upgrade, heidi uninstall


Don't choose .local directory (we don't want extra project-local state folders).
